==================================================================================================================
                                      DATeS: Data Assimilation Testing Suite                                      
==================================================================================================================

DATeS is aimed to be a unified testing suite for data assimilation applications where researchers can collaborate, 
so that it would be much easier to understand and compare different methodologies in different settings.
  
The core of DATeS is implemented in Python to enable for Object-Oriented capabilities. 
The main functionalities, such as the models, the data assimilation algorithms, the linear algebra solvers, and 
the time discretization routines are independent of each other, such as to offer maximum flexibility to configure 
data assimilation applications.
DATeS can interface easily with large third party models written in Fortran or C, & with various external solvers.

==================================================================================================================
